<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Public Administration Select Committee Submission – Crime Statistics</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from the</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Police and Crime Commissioner for Bedfordshire</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> [CST0071]</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.74pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I welcome the Committee’s recent inquiry into crime statistics, but also recognise the incongruity between the fall in the accepted measures of crime (CSEW and recorded crime) and the experience of both frontline police officers who have not benefited from a parallel reduction in demand, and the public who pay little attention to either measure of crime as their day to day experience of </span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">low level crime and ASB does not tally. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Putting the Public First</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.74pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The public of Bedfordshire do not tell me that they are worried by absolut</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">e or relative levels of crime. Instead, t</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">hey tell me that they do not often see their police, particularly within rural communities, and black and minority ethnic communities tell me that they are less likely to engage with or report incidents to the police, and be less satisfied with the service that they receive from them if they do.</span></li><li style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.74pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">It is for </span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">this reason that my focus has been to take concrete steps to build on the past success of the neighbourhood policing model, and put a the heart of my</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> police and crime plan</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> the desire to reconnect the public with their police by coining the phrase “Confident Communities”, and set</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ting</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> out an agenda which seeks to be a 21</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> century iteration of the </span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Peelian</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> principle that the police are the public and the public are the police. This programme of work is outcome driven, and whilst there are a number of metrics that can be used to assess the impact of work undertaken, these are </span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ends and not the means by which the success of this programme will be judged.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Reality Check</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.74pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#030303; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">More widely, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I am well aware</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> of concerns about the impact of target setting in policing.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I have not</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> set targets for Bedfordshire Police or </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">any </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">other </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">community safety or criminal justice </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">agencies.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> To focus resources effectively </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">my </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Chief Constable</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> and I </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">have agreed stretching ‘ambitions’ </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">which are benchmarked by moving national averages rather than static binary comparisons.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.74pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I therefore </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">take a rounded view of performance, understanding that the quality of service the public receive is more complex than a basket of performance indicators can adequately reflect.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Alongside the quantitative and qualitative information </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> receive from Bedfordshire Police and other partners, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> undertake a number of community engagement activities each week to hear directly from local people.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">I find this ‘reality check’ hugely important </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to understand </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">impact </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">of crime and ASB on local communities, and whether the steps being taken to address their concerns are appropriate and positive.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Crime Recording</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.74pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">In terms of the audit and governance of crime recording I am pleased that within Bedfordshire there are robust processes and checks in place. We have a risk assessed audit programme and are currently looking at using a number of experienced gatekeepers to review crimes at key decision points. Additionally, the members of the audit team report into the force governance structure to ensure management oversight.</span></li><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.74pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">All this allows me to say that the vast majority of crimes reported to Bedfordshire Police are being recorded correctly. Our incident to crime rate is assessed as above 90% in the majority of crime categories. Once recorded, we are correctly categorising crimes with 98% accuracy</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:115%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 14.11pt; padding-left:3.74pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Declaration of Interest as requested for Written Submissions can be found at </span><a href="http://www.bedfordshire.pcc.police.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/REGISTER-OF-INTERESTS-PCC-amended-250213.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bedfordshire.pcc.police.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/REGISTER-OF-INTERESTS-PCC-amended-250213.pdf</span></a></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>